=Lǐ Hè 李賀 (790-816)=
==Literature==
===PhD Dissertations===
* David Ying Ch'en: Li Ho and Keats: A Comparative Study of Two Poets. Indiana University, 1962
* Maureen A. Robertson: Poetic Diction in the Works of Li Ho (791-817). University of Washington, 1970
* Michael B. Fish: Mythological Themes in the Poetry of Li Ho (791-817). Indiana University, 1973
* Kuo-ch'ing Tu: The Poetry of Li Ho: A Critical Study. Stanford University, 1974
* Kuniko Ukai: Songs of a Hidden Orchid: Yuefu and Gexing by Li He (791-817). University Leiden, 2008
===Monographs===
* Margaret T. South: Li Ho, A Scholar Official of the Yüan-ho Period 806-821. Adelaide: Libraries Board of South Australia, 1967
* Naotarō Kudō: The Life and Thoughts of Li Ho. Tokyo: Waseda University Press, 1969
* J.D. Frodsham: The Poems of Li Ho (791-817). Oxford: Clarendon Press, 1970
* Kuo-ch'ing Tu: Li Ho. Boston: Twayne Publishers, 1979
===Articles===
* Michael B. Fish: The Striving of Young Man at Twenty: Li Ho's Poem "Wildly Singing". in Critical Essays on Chinese Literature, Nienhauser eds. Hong Kong: The Chinese University of Hong Kong, 1976
